name: The Metaverse
description: In this game, the Metaverse refers to an alternate reality where the cognition of society manifests into physical creations. This can directly reflect the mental desires of an individual if their perception of themselves is too distorted. For example, someone in a position of power in the real world might appear as a literal king in a castle in the Metaverse, ruling over their subjects.

name: Tokyo, Japan
description: Tokyo is the capital of Japan, and the most heavily populated prefecture in the country, and the single most populous individual city in the world.

name: Boletaria
description: The fictional continent of Boletaria, where the game takes place, has been corrupted by dark powers that have twisted and altered the inhabitants into demons. Nobody can get in or out without passing through the Nexus.

name: The Nexus
description: A place between places, the Nexus is where wandering souls meet and gather as either sanctuary or travelling between worlds.

name: Arrakis
description: Arrakis, or "Dune" as it is colloquially referred to, is the most important planet in the sphere of the Imperium's control. Home to the Fremen, the indigenous inhabitants of the planet, as well as the gargantuan sandworms that roam beneath the planet's boundless sands to create its valuable resource known as Spice.

name: Arkham City
description: Located within Gotham City, the Arkham City prison has taken a few districts in Gotham and walled them off to create one large maximum security prison complex. There are no rules except not attempting to escape, which has led to the criminal factions taking over and creating their own lawless territory.

name: Gotham City
description: A fictional city in America, Gotham City is known for its architectural beauty, business centers, and cultural hubs just as much as it is for crime, corruption, and villainy. The city is in a near constant tug of war between the criminal gangs and the city's law enforcement, but even the police have criminals within who deal in bribery and information gathering for the villains. However, it is not all doom and gloom, as the city has been home to a number of vigilantes and well meaning individuals over the years trying to make it a better place.

name: El Dorado
description: While the modern mythology of "The City of Gold" is one of fantasy and legend, the story of Uncharted offers its own turn on the legend. The city was largely prosperous, but fell to an unknown disaster, leaving it lost to time unless you know where to find it.

name: The Golden Isle
description: The Golden Isle is an amalgamation of all of the ancient Greek myths, found in one vast location. Across the island one might encounter a god, a roaming pack of animals, or ancient monsters along with other secrets and puzzles to encounter.

name: The Last City
description: The last major city on Earth in the far future. Set up by survivors and refugees of the Collapse, a devastating calamity in the game's universe, the Last City is home to humans, exos, and awoken alike. Presided over by the Vanguard, an organization that coordinates Guardian activities across the solar system, it has stood for many centuries, but safety has never been guaranteed despite the city defenses.

name: The Underground
description: The Underground is the long forgotten world inhabited by monsters who used to live with humanity many years past. It is possible for humans to find their way in, but it has been impossible for any monsters to leave for many years. Because of this, the Underground has grown into its own unique civilization with monsters of all kinds living in relative harmony with one another.

name: Inkwell Isle
description: The home of Cuphead, Mugman, and a variety of other quirky animated characters. Stylized after the cartoons of the 1930s and 40s, Inkwell Isle holds many secrets and dangers for the game's main duo to overcome.

name: Earth
description: Home to a wide variety of plants, animals, and cultures, Earth is the place we all call home. It has a great deal to offer to everyone who inhabits it. Humanity has adapted and thrived on it for countless years, developing their own cultures and ways of life.

name: The Wastelands
description: Originally created by the sorcerer Yen Sid, the Wasteland was meant to be a place for lost and forgotten characters to live their lives peacefully and in a relative utopia. However, after Mickey causes the Thinner Disaster and accidentally destroys most of it, the land has been forever twisted and changed into a darker reflection of that initial idea.

name: Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry
description: Located in the English countryside in a magically protected area, Hogwarts is where young witches and wizards go to learn all about the magical world. Having been established centuries ago, the school is a large, sprawling castle complex that houses dorms, classrooms, and no end of secret passages in its ancient walls.

name: Hogsmeade
description: A small hamlet just outside of Hogwarts, this town is home to a variety of magical shops for students of the school to frequent, peruse, and purchase from. It has a small personality of its own with its slightly twisted and off-kilter architecture, holding a number of secrets and interesting sights.

name: Alterna
description: The land of Alterna is home to snow capped peaks and frosty environs, inhabited by a number of new mammalian creatures. The Squidlings venture into the land in order to find out about a possible new threat to the world.

name: Inkopolis
description: Inkopolis is a large metropolitan area, home to a number of Squidlings going about their daily lives or participating in the Splatfest competition to prove their mettle. The city is fairly utopian, sponsoring friendly contests and collaboration among the citizens.

name: Destiny Islands
description: The home world of Sora and Riku, Destiny Islands is the place where the two of them would hang out alongside a few other friends from the mainland. It's characterized by its sandy shores, vibrant blue waters, and the unique paopu fruit trees that grow across its surface.

name: Olliewood
description: While the name is a skateboard focused pun on "Hollywood", this small town is home to a number of skateboarding inhabitants who complete and try to show up one another in friendly rivalries. There is also a handful of other quirky townsfolk with miscellaneous tasks they need help completing. Aside from this, they have strange, film reel portals that can transport the player to a handful of worlds from Disney films, each with their own skate-centric designs.

name: Tamriel
description: The main continent in which the series takes place, Tamriel is home to all manner of creatures from the mundane to the fantastical.

name: Cyrodiil
description: The capital nation of the human Imperium on Tamriel, Cyrodiil is comprised of lush green hills and valleys, a handful of minor cities, and the Imperial Capital at its center. While being the main cultural hub of humans, a variety of other races and species can be found engaging in commerce, diplomacy, or even underhanded actions.

name: Meridian
description: The capital city for the Carja tribe and main hub in Horizon Zero Dawn, Meridian is home to the Sun King and his court. It hosts a number of dignitaries, traders, and builders from all across the land, now a thriving trade hub in the mesas and deserts.

name: Lordran
description: A dark fantasy setting that is home to all manner dangers, be it human or monster, now fallen to ruin as the First Flame fades. In its golden age, it was ruled over by the Four Lords, each with their own designated lands within the country. It consists of deep catacombs, poisonous swamps, cluttered villages, and a sprawling capital city.

name: Night City
description: A city located on the coast of California, Night City is host to millions of people. The city is embroiled in a near-constant state of gang warfare, corporate exploitation and espionage, and political corruption. Within this structure, the basic understanding is that you should expect to live for a fun time, not a long time.

name: Duckburg
description: The main hometown of Scrooge McDuck and his nephews, the city of Duckburg is home to inventors, evil-doers, heroes, and other quirky characters.

name: The Milky Way Galaxy
description: The galaxy in which our solar system of Sol and a multitude of others reside. A place which we still know very little about, but each expedition can help to change that.

name: Forest
description: A large area of land covered chiefly with trees and undergrowth.

name: Sandy beach
description: Where the protagonist decides to have a picnic.

name: Front yard
description: With grass where the protagonist lands his balloon.

name: Cave
description: The cave is where the dragon lived behind a large door.

name: Castle
description: The castle where Princess Elizabeth lives.

name: Castle
description: The castle where Princess Elizabeth lives.

name: Cave
description: The cave is where the dragon lived behind a large door.

name: Inaba, Japan
description: A rural mountain town in Japan, inspired by town in the floodplains regions around Mount Fuji.

name: The Mushroom Kingdom
description: The homeland of Princess Peach and her Toadstool citizens.

name: Rapture
description: The undersea city of Rapture was conceived by wealthy businessman Andrew Ryan as a utopia for free enterprise and objectivist ideas; however the lack of any regulations caused anarchy to rule in the end.

name: Unexplored Galaxy
description: The galaxy is unexplored and mysterious, relying on exploration to unveil its secrets, both beneficial and dangerous.

name: Stardew Valley
description: A small, rural town in the countryside, Stardew Valley is home to a variety of plants to grow, animals to domesticate, people to meet, and caves to explore.

name: The Kingdom of Hyrule
description: A fantasy kingdom under the watch of Princess Zelda and magically protected by powerful spirit guardians.

name: Down by the river
description: A tugboat can be found down by the river and this is also where a cement bags can be found.

name: London
description: London is the capital city of England and the United Kingdom and where Mack the Knife lives.

name: England
description: Mack the Knife is from England, a country located on the island of Great Britain, which is part of the British Isles. England is one of the four constituent countries of the United Kingdom, along with Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland.

name: Club
description: An establishment for nighttime entertainment, typically serving drinks and offering music, dancing, etc. The singer says "The club isn't the best place to find a lover."

name: Bar
description: A bar, also known as a saloon, a tavern or tippling house, or sometimes as a pub or club, is a retail business establishment that serves alcoholic beverages, such as beer, wine, liquor, cocktails, and other beverages such as mineral water and soft drinks. The singer does to the bar with friends to find someone to love and drink shots, dance and talk

name: Bikini Bottom
description: A small, undersea city home to a variety of fish folk of all kinds.

name: Ghost Island
description: The island home to the many ghosts that constantly pester and antagonize Pac-Man.

name: New York City
description: The "City that Never Sleeps", located in downstate New York, is one of the cultural capitals of the United States.

name: Eos
description: An Earth-like world where the convenience and technology of the near future blends with the magical and fantastical world of swords and sorcery, defended by the gods and ruled over by a number of warring kingdoms.

name: The Holy Land
description: The site of modern day Israel, this descriptor was used to denote the geographical focus of the Crusades.

name: Backseat
description: The term "backseat" generally refers to the rear seating area of a vehicle, such as a car, truck, or van.

name: Room (Bed)
description: This is a room furnished with a bed and intended primarily for sleeping.

name: Spanish Harlem
description: East Harlem, also known as Spanish Harlem or El Barrio, is a neighborhood of Upper Manhattan in New York City, north of the Upper East Side and bounded by 96th Street to the south, Fifth Avenue to the west, and the East and Harlem Rivers to the east and north.

name: Barrio
description: Barrio is a Spanish word that means "quarter" or "neighborhood". In the modern Spanish language, it is generally defined as each area of a city, usually delimited by functional (e.g. residential, commercial, industrial, etc.), social, architectural or morphological features.

name: World
description: The earth, together with all of its countries, peoples, and natural features.

name: Sky
description: The region of the atmosphere and outer space seen from the earth.

name: New York
description: New York can refer to a state or city. New York state is in the northeastern US; population 19.84 million (est. 2021); capital, Albany. New York City major city and port in southeastern New York, situated on the Atlantic coast at the mouth of the Hudson River; population 8.468(est. 2021).

name: San Francisco
description: San Francisco is a city and seaport in western California, on the coast, on a peninsula between the Pacific Ocean and San Francisco Bay; population 815,201 (est. 2021). The city suffered severe damage from earthquakes in 1906 and in 1989

name: Disco
description: A club or party at which people dance to recorded pop music.

name: Mr. Utterson’s Residence
description: 15 Gaunt St. London, England (Non existing at the writing of the novella)

name: Farm
description: This story takes place on a traditional farm. The story primarily takes place in and around the barn where the animals reside.

name: The Great Green Room
description: The majority of the book is set within the confines of the young rabbit's room. The room is filled with various objects and furnishings, including a fireplace, a bowl of mush, a red balloon, a telephone, a dollhouse, a pair of mittens, a quiet old lady, and more.

name: Doorway
description: An entrance to a room or building through a door.

name: Watchtower
description: A tower built to create an elevated observation point and depicts a place where people in charge observe and control the actions of others.

name: Middle of Nowhere
description: An extremely distant, remote, and isolated location.

name: Vault or tomb of Capulet family
Monaster Verona ( near Friar Laurence's cell)
Hertfordshire
description: The county, where Longbourn, Netherfield, and Meryton are all located.

name: Hunsford
description: The town where Charlotte and Mr. Collins live.

name: Sushi restaurant
description: A place where people pay to sit and eat Sushi, a Japanese dish that features tiny pieces of raw fish wrapped in rice and seaweed. which is cooked and served on the premises.

name: The Star Wars Galaxy
description: The main galaxy in which the stories of the Star Wars universe take place.

name: Kitchen
description: The family is gathered at the breakfast table, except for Amy.

name: school
description: Amy is taken to school in her bed while still sleeping.

name: gym
description: Amy is taken to the gym in her bed during school while her classmates played basketball.

name: Granbois
description: The Cosway estate outside Massacre, Dominica

name: The Place where The Wild Things are
In the closet
description: A closet is an enclosed space, with a door, used for storage, particularly that of clothes.

name: Lighthouse
description: Erected on a hill between the towns of Puttenham and Elstead in the English county of Surrey, south of the Hog’s Back ridge.

name: New Mexico Savage Reservation
description: West of Albuquerque, New Mexico, encompassing the Malpais Valley

name: Park Lane Hospital for the Dying
Front porch
description: A front porch is a covered platform that extends from the front entrance of a house or building, typically located before the main entrance. It serves as a transitional space between the private interior of a home and the public outdoor environment.

name: Living Room
description: A room in a house for general and informal everyday use.

name: Lawn
description: An area of short, mown grass in a yard, garden, or park.

name: Bathroom
description: A room containing a toilet and sink and typically also a bathtub or shower.

name: Beach
description: A strip of land covered with sand, pebbles, or small stones at the edge of a body of water, especially by the ocean between high- and low-water mark.

name: Cassiar Bar
description: Location of a small settlement in the Yukon Territory directly on the Yukon River.

name: Chilkoot Trail
description: The Chilkoot Trail or Chilkoot Pass, also called the Dyea Pass, was a dangerous route leading from Dyea, Alaska, to the Yukon Territory's lakes region that led to the coveted Klondike River.

name: Dawson City
description: Located at the mouth of the Klondike River where it meets the Yukon River, Dawson City was named after George Dawson, who explored the region with the Canadian Geological Survey in 1887; nicknamed the 'Paris of the North' due to the bustling activity here that centered greatly upon the mining industry, because of its proximity to the Klondike River.

name: Dyea
description: A booming town in Alaska built on the banks of the Taiya River located ten miles north of Skaguay.

name: Forty Mile Creek
description: A dangerous river in the Yukon Territory

name: Queen Charlotte Sound
description: A body of water between Seattle, Washington and along the western coast of British Columbia, located in the Pacific Ocean.

name: Santa Clara Valley
description: A region of California located about forty miles south of San Francisco. The largest urban area in the Santa Clara Valley is modern day San Jose.

name: Seattle
description: Located in northwestern Washington, this coastal city is the last stop for many travelers before they enter Alaska, whether it is by train or by boat. Traveling miners bought supplies in Seattle, newly discovered gold capital flowed into the city from the north, and lumber from the rich forests around the city was shipped into Alaska to build new settlements for the miners there. Seattle continued to prosper even when the Gold Rush ended and the influx of people slowed down.

name: Skaguay
description: Today known as Skagway, a popular city for miners to gain entry to the Yukon Territory's Klondike region by braving the White Pass, running parallel to the more treacherous Chilkoot Pass to the north.

name: Stewart river
description: A river located in the unsettled regions of the Yukon Territory south of Dawson City, flowing eastward parallel to the Klondike River. The Stewart River branches off of the Yukon River.

name: Thirty Mile river
description: The Thirty Mile River (which is the Yukon River) begins where the Chilkoot Pass ends, leading directly to Dawson City, where the Yukon River forms a junction with the gold-rich Klondike River.

name: Yukon Territory
description: First explored in 1846 by the Hudson's Bay Company, the Yukon Territory of Canada is located east of Alaska, West of the Northwest Territories, and north of British Columbia; from the Loucheux word 'Yukunah,' meaning 'great river,' because the Yukon River is so large.

name: Courtyard
description: An unroofed area that is completely or mostly enclosed by the walls of a large building

name: Labrador
description: A Christian fundamentalist civilization which arose in North America centuries after a nuclear holocaust

name: Lyme
description: Dorset town on the southern coast of England

name: Seale
description: Resort town on southeastern England’s Kentish coast

name: Dance Floor
description: An area of floor in a nightclub, disco, or restaurant that is reserved for dancing.

name: Chink's Basin
description: A section of the Thames River above Gravesend

name: Avignon
description: A city in South East France near the confluence of the Rhone and Durance rivers.

name: Bologna
description: Industrial town in north-central Italy, at the foot of the Apennines, that becomes the major target of squadron bombing raids.

name: Military Hospital Pianosa
description: Military hospital in Pianosa in which the novel opens and to which it periodically returns; it is the refuge to which Army Air Force captain John Yossarian, the protagonist, escapes whenever the stress of dealing with the war and “catch-22” overcomes him.

name: Pianosa
description: Tiny island in Tuscan archipelago, off the west-central coast of Italy, near Elba and Corsica, in the Mediterranean Sea, on which Yossarian’s bomber squadron is stationed.

name: Ellen Olenska’s house in New York.
Abame
description: A village destroyed by white men because they killed one white man.

name: Evil Forest
description: The Evil Forest is located across the stream from the village where anything that was not condoned by the religion of Umuofia was sent, including men who killed themselves, ogbanje, and twins.

name: Great River
description: West Africa’s biggest river, rising in Guinea and flowing generally east before turning southward to flow through Nigeria.

name: Mbaino
description: Village bordering on Umofia. Umofia and Mbaino are traditional enemies.

name: Mbanta
description: Okonkwo’s mother’s village, just beyond Mbaino, where Okonkwo spends his seven years of exile.

name: Okonkwo’s compound
description: The home of Okonkwo and his immediate family.

name: Umofia
description: Area in southeastern Nigeria, comprising nine villages, where the Umofia clan live

name: Shed
description: A shed is typically a simple, single-story roofed structure that is used for hobbies, or as a workshop in a back garden or on an allotment.

name: Museum of Natural History, New York
Sin City
description: A common nickname for Las Vegas, Nevada, USA that is an urban area (a city or part of) that caters to various vices. These vices may be legal (depending on area) or illegal activities which are tolerated.

name: Tatooine
description: A desert planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim, Tatooine is home to Luke Skywalker and his family. It is known for its remoteness and as a safe harbor for smugglers and gangsters, like the Hutt crime family. Famous cities include Mos Eisley.

name: Alderaan
description: A peaceful planet in the galaxy's Mid Rim region, Alderaan is known for its wealth and beautiful environments. It is the home world to Princess Leia and her family, and it is destroyed by the Galactic Empire as a test of their new weapon, the Death Star.

name: Yavin 4
description: Fourth moon of the gas giant planet, Yavin. This is the location of a secret Rebel Alliance base that serves as the launching point for their attack on the Death Star. It is covered in lush forests and has numerous, ancient temples.

name: Mos Eisley
description: The largest trading port on the planet of Tatooine, Mos Eisley is the place for someone to hide from the Empire, hire a ride off world, or trade their wares. It is extremely unsafe as bounty hunters, criminals, and Imperial Stormtroopers roam the streets. As Ben Kenobi describes it, "You will never find a more wretched hive of scum and villainy. We must be cautious."

name: Lars Homestead
description: This farm on the planet of Tatooine is the home to Luke Skywalker. Founded by Owen and Beru Lars (Luke's uncle and aunt), its main product is moisture evaporation from the arid surface of the planet.

name: University of Notre Dame Southn Bend Indiana
description: A Top University in the United States with one of the premier football programs in the country.

name: Greenbow, Alabama
description: Fictional farmland town where Forrest Gump grew up.

name: Bayou la Batre
description: Like Greenbow, Bayou la Batre is also in Alabama. However, Bayou la Batre is a real shrimp town. This is where Forrest Gump and Lieutenant Dan establish their shrimp boat company.

name: Mekong Delta, Vietnam
description: Mekong Delta is where Forrest Gump goes when he joins the Army, Here, he meets Benjamin Buford "Bubba" Blue and Lieutenant Dan Taylor.

name: The Underworld
description: The Underworld is a dark and foreboding realm in Greek mythology, ruled by Hades, the god of the dead. It is depicted as a vast and shadowy realm located deep beneath the earth, where the souls of the deceased reside for eternity. The Underworld is divided into various regions, including the Fields of Asphodel, where ordinary souls dwell, and the Elysian Fields, a paradise reserved for heroes and the virtuous. Additionally, there are darker areas such as Tartarus, a pit of eternal punishment for the most wicked souls. The Underworld is often portrayed as a place of gloom and despair, with rivers like the Styx and the Lethe flowing through it, and guarded by creatures such as Cerberus, the three-headed dog. It plays a significant role in Greek mythology as the destination of souls after death and as a setting for various myths and legends.

name: Camp Half-Blood
description: Camp Half-Blood is a sanctuary and training ground for demigods, individuals who are the offspring of a Greek god and a mortal. Located on Long Island, New York, the camp serves as a refuge for these half-bloods, providing them with a safe haven to learn about their heritage, develop their abilities, and train for the dangers of the world. The camp is hidden from mortal view by magical barriers, ensuring its secrecy and protection from outside threats. It is equipped with various facilities, including cabins for each godly parent, training grounds for combat and other skills, and communal areas for socializing and recreation.

name: The Lotus Hotel and Casino
description: The Lotus Hotel and Casino is a luxurious establishment located in Las Vegas, Nevada, featured in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. Despite its opulent appearance, the hotel is actually a trap for unsuspecting mortals and demigods. Time within the Lotus Hotel operates differently, causing guests to lose track of time and become ensnared in its pleasures indefinitely. Inside the hotel, guests are pampered with lavish accommodations, gourmet cuisine, and endless entertainment, including arcade games and shows. However, the true danger lies in the addictive nature of the lotus flowers served in various forms, which induce a state of euphoria and complacency, trapping guests in a perpetual cycle of leisure and distraction.

name: The Parthenon
description: The Parthenon is an ancient temple located on the Acropolis of Athens, Greece, dedicated to the goddess Athena, the city's patron deity. Built in the 5th century BCE, it is regarded as one of the most iconic symbols of ancient Greek civilization and is renowned for its architectural brilliance and historical significance. The Parthenon is a Doric-style temple constructed primarily of marble, featuring a grand facade adorned with intricate sculptures and ornate friezes depicting scenes from Greek mythology. The temple's design embodies the principles of classical Greek architecture, with its symmetrical proportions, columned porticos, and pedimental sculptures.

name: The Gateway Arch
description: The Gateway Arch is an iconic monument located in St. Louis, Missouri, USA. Designed by architect Eero Saarinen, it stands as a symbol of the westward expansion of the United States and commemorates St. Louis's role as the "Gateway to the West." Completed in 1965, the Gateway Arch is the tallest arch in the world, soaring 630 feet (192 meters) into the sky. Its sleek, stainless steel structure forms an inverted, weighted catenary arch, supported by triangular legs on each side.

name: The Empire State Building
description: The Empire State Building is a historic skyscraper located in Midtown Manhattan, New York City. Completed in 1931, it stood as the tallest building in the world until the completion of the North Tower of the World Trade Center in 1970. Rising to a height of 1,454 feet (443.2 meters) at its tip, the Empire State Building is renowned for its distinctive Art Deco design and iconic silhouette. It features a prominent spire at its summit, which is illuminated with various colors on special occasions.

name: Convenience Store
description: A convenience store, bodega, convenience shop, corner store or corner shop is a small retail store that stocks a range of everyday items such as tea, coffee, groceries, fruits, vegetables, snacks, confectionery, soft drinks, ice creams, tobacco products, lottery tickets, over-the-counter drugs, toiletries, newspapers and magazines

name: Shelter
description: A place giving temporary protection from bad weather or danger.

name: Suburbs
description: An outlying district of a city, especially a residential one.

name: Market
description: A regular gathering of people for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other commodities.

name: Balcony
description: A balcony is a platform projecting from the wall of a building, supported by columns or console brackets, and enclosed with a balustrade, usually above the ground floor.

name: A town
description: A n urban area that has a name, defined boundaries, and local government, and that is generally larger than a village and smaller than a city.

name: Small Terminid Nest
description: A small number of Terminid bug holes in the ground that routinely spawn Terminids, with the amount and types of Terminids dependent on the difficulty of missions.

name: Spore Spewer
description: Tall mushroom-like structures that eject spores into the atmosphere which causes a dense fog around themselves, obscuring visibility in the area.

name: Large Terminid Nest
description: A vast crater-like structure in the ground, or a large pillar-like structure that contains multiple holes where Terminids spawn with much larger and more difficult types of Terminids defending the area. When the nest consists of pillars, it also contains eggs that Helldivers must typically destroy.

name: Automaton Fabricator
description: The Fabricator periodically spawns Troopers of various kinds until it’s destroyed. Fabricators are typically surrounded by Automaton infantry and other strong automaton-types.

name: Cannon Towers
description: Cannon Towers serve as automated defense structures, guarding key locations within Automaton-controlled areas. They are equipped with powerful energy cannons capable of dealing significant damage to intruders.

name: Detector Towers
description: The Detector Tower resembles a large eye observing its surroundings. It slowly rotates, scanning for any signs of intruders, once a player is spotted by the Detector Tower, it will cry out for reinforcements. Enemy Dropships will continuously arrive until the tower is destroyed. This makes the Detector Tower an extremely dangerous sub-objective during missions.

name: Command Bunkers
description: Command Bunkers serve as central hubs for Automaton operations. They coordinate reinforcements, tactical decisions, and overall strategy. Destroying a Command Bunker disrupts their communication network and weakens their forces.

name: Stratagem Jammer
description: The Stratagem Jammer interferes with your ability to call down Stratagems during missions. When near a jammer, you won’t be able to access certain powerful reinforcements or support tools. Disabling it is essential for mission success.

name: Mortar Emplacement
description: The Automaton Mortar Emplacement is one of the side objectives encountered during missions. These emplacements are fortified positions equipped with specialized mortar turrets. Mortars within these emplacements constantly rain down explosive shells on the team’s general area. The relentless bombardment can disrupt movement, hinder objectives, and pose a significant threat to Helldivers.

name: Gunship Facility
description: Gunships can keep coming due to nearby Gunship Facilities. These facilities continuously produce Gunships during missions. At higher difficulties, multiple Gunships may appear simultaneously, making them even more challenging.
